- The integer array parameter `nums` must not be null.
- The integer array parameter `nums` length is greater than or equal to 2 and is less than or equal to 100000.
- All values in the integer array parameter `nums` are greater than or equal to 1 and are less than or equal to 100.
- The integer array parameter `queries` must not be null.
- The length of the integer array parameter `queries` is greater than or equal to 1 and is less than or equal to 20000.
- The integer array result `ans` length is equal to the length of the integer array parameter `queries`.
- Each element in the integer array result `ans` is the minimum absolute difference of the subarray `nums[li...ri]` containing the elements of `nums` between the 0-based indices `li` and `ri` (inclusive).
- The value of the minimum absolute difference is calculated as `|x|` where `x` is the difference between two elements in the subarray.